      "detail": "Data relevance and commercial value decay over time as new information emerges, markets evolve, and knowledge becomes outdated or displaced. Infrastructure financed around today's data assets may need to be served by completely different data sources within a few years of commissioning. Perishable value dynamics mean data licence renewal at commercially reasonable terms is not guaranteed across the infrastructure lifecycle. The infrastructure may outlast the period during which its original training data remains competitively valuable and commercially relevant."
    },
