      "detail": "The infrastructure serves a core business function rather than an experimental initiative, meaning its financial performance is material to organisational health. Core dependency means the lifecycle mismatch directly affects the organisation's financial stability, creditworthiness, and strategic options if gaps materialise. Infrastructure failure, underutilisation, or stranded capacity from lifecycle misalignment has material consequences for the entire business and its stakeholders. The revenue stakes make lifecycle management a mission-critical governance function rather than a routine operational concern."
